                    <div class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1488911990223-why-is-there-different-community-representation-included-for-comparison-with-different-equity-groups-" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#0e59497d-323a-49b8-bec4-1b097313da9d" href="#accordion-content-1488911990223-why-is-there-different-community-representation-included-for-comparison-with-different-equity-groups-" aria-controls="accordion-content-1488911990223-why-is-there-different-community-representation-included-for-comparison-with-different-equity-groups-" aria-expanded="false">
                            Why is there different community representation included for comparison with different equity groups?
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1488911990223-why-is-there-different-community-representation-included-for-comparison-with-different-equity-groups-" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1488911990223-why-is-there-different-community-representation-included-for-comparison-with-different-equity-groups-">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1488911990223 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="781475a9-a928-4752-bc22-817698849025" >

    <p>This is largely due to the availability of data about larger community representation outside of Ryerson.</p> 
<p>Most of the community representation data comes from Statistics Canada, from the National Household Survey (NHS), censuses or special surveys, which currently only provide Ontario representation data for persons with disabilities.</p> 
<p>While we do have data from Statistics Canada on the representation of Aboriginal peoples in the GTA, given the fact that many Aboriginal peoples live in indigenous communities outside of the GTA, the Ontario data is included in the report as well.</p> 
<p>Statistics Canada's NHS and Census data currently does not provide information about the representation of&nbsp;the 2SLGBTQ+ community. However, the Toronto Public Health survey conducted in 2001 provides some idea of the representation of this group in the city, even if it is outdated.</p>
    





</div>
