                    <div class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1488911991741-where-does-the-comparison-data-on-representation-of-equity-groups-in-the-gta--ontario-and-canada-come-from-" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#0e59497d-323a-49b8-bec4-1b097313da9d" href="#accordion-content-1488911991741-where-does-the-comparison-data-on-representation-of-equity-groups-in-the-gta--ontario-and-canada-come-from-" aria-controls="accordion-content-1488911991741-where-does-the-comparison-data-on-representation-of-equity-groups-in-the-gta--ontario-and-canada-come-from-" aria-expanded="false">
                            Where does the comparison data on representation of equity groups in the GTA, Ontario and Canada come from?
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1488911991741-where-does-the-comparison-data-on-representation-of-equity-groups-in-the-gta--ontario-and-canada-come-from-" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1488911991741-where-does-the-comparison-data-on-representation-of-equity-groups-in-the-gta--ontario-and-canada-come-from-">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1488911991741 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="a5d46c3d-f9fb-4b3d-9b1a-16a0426e64e3" >

    <p><strong>Data about Aboriginal Peoples, women and racialized people</strong></p> 
<p>The GTA and Ontario data used to compare representation of Aboriginal employees, women and racialized employees at Ryerson comes from the 2011 National Household Survey (NHS) data produced by Statistics Canada.</p> 
<p><strong>Data about employees with disabilities</strong></p> 
<p>The Ontario data used to compare representation of employees with disabilities at Ryerson comes from the 2012 Statistics Canada survey on persons with disabilities in Canada.</p> 
<p><strong>Data about 2SLGBTQ+ employees</strong></p> 
<p>Toronto data used for comparison with the representation of 2SLGBTQ+ employees at Ryerson comes from a 2001 Toronto Public Health survey.</p>
    





</div>
